Wedding season is upon us, and while we promise we are all completely over the moon for our friends who have managed to escape the tumbleweed-filled wastelands of dating apps, we do have some gripes.   Now we know our contribution is a drop in the ocean compared to how much the bride and groom will be shelling out, but given we aren't the ones who will end up with a ring on our finger at the end, we feel we have a right to be a little tighter with the purse strings. So here are 11 do's and don'ts for the bride when trying to organise a hen party and not lose all your friends in the process.           